&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;University Hospital of North Midlands NHS Trust&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Consultant in Colorectal and General Surgery &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applications are invited for a Consultant Colorectal &amp; General Surgeon at the University Hospital of North Midlands NHS Trust (UHNM).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;University Hospital of North Midlands is a large acute teaching hospital and major trauma centre in Staffordshire with two sites- Royal Stoke University Hospital in Stoke on Trent and County Hospital in Stafford. UHNM offers a broad range of medical and surgical specialties We have good transport links, being close to the M6 and A50, and lie roughly centrally between Manchester and Birmingham to the North and South, and Derby and Shrewsbury to the East and West.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a dynamic, high calibre Colorectal Surgeon. You must be able to deliver first class clinical care and be prepared to participate fully in the development of our service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post has been established to strengthen colorectal services provided due to increased local demand. The appointee would be expected to have close working relationship with Upper GI, Gastroenterology, Emergency Department and Paediatric colleagues. There is on call and ward cover included in this role.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Closing date: 1st December 2020&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interview Date: 7th January 2021&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
